==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gadolinite
<hw>Gad"o*lin*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
<etsep>Gadolin</etsep>, a Russian chemist.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of a nearly black color and vitreous luster, and
consisting principally of the silicates of yttrium, cerium, and
iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gadolinium</ent>⟦br⟧
